merican and Canadian football)|DT]]\n|-\n|[[1997 NFL season|1997]]||[[Warrick Dunn]] ||[[Running back|RB]]\n|-\n|[[2005 NFL season|2005]]||[[Cadillac Williams]] ||[[Running back|RB]]\n|-\n|[[2015 NFL season|2015]]||[[Jameis Winston]] ||[[Quarterback|QB]]\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\" nowrap|'''NFL Offensive Rookie of the Year Award'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n|-\n|[[1997 NFL season|1997]]||[[Warrick Dunn]] ||[[Running back|RB]]\n|-\n|[[2005 NFL season|2005]]||[[Cadillac Williams]] ||[[Running Back|RB]]\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''NFL Comeback Player of the Year'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n|-\n|[[2008 NFL season|2008]]||[[Antonio Bryant]]  ||[[Wide receiver|WR]]\n|-\n|[[2013 NFL season|2013]]||[[Darrelle Revis]] ||[[Cornerback|CB]]\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\" nowrap|'''Maxwell Club NFL Coach of the Year'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Coach\n|-\n|[[1997 NFL season|1997]]||[[Tony Dungy]]\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''[[Bart Starr Award|<span style=\"{{NFLSecondaryColor|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\">Bart Starr Award</span>]]'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n|-\n|[[2004 NFL season|2004]]||[[Derrick Brooks]] ||[[Linebacker|LB]]\n|-\n|[[2009 NFL season|2009]]||[[Warrick Dunn]] ||[[Running back|RB]]\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Byron \"Whizzer\" White NFL Man of the Year Award'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n|-\n|[[1997 NFL season|1997]]||[[Hardy Nickerson]]  ||[[Linebacker|LB]]\n|-\n|[[2003 NFL season|2003]]||[[Derrick Brooks]]  ||[[Linebacker|LB]]\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\" nowrap|'''Walter Payton NFL Man of the Year Award'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Season\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n|-\n|[[2000 NFL season|2000]]||[[Derrick Brooks]]  ||[[Linebacker|LB]]\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Tampa Stadium Krewe of Honor===\nIn 1991, the organization initiated the \"Krewe of Honor\" to recognize top players, and featured a mural of the first class of three members.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tampa initiates Krewe of Honor|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/7633747//|first=Ed|last=Werder|newspaper=The Orlando Sentinel|page=42|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|date=December 5, 1991|accessdate=November 28, 2016}}{{Open access}}</ref> The display was located on the east side of the stadium. Quarterback Doug Williams was inducted September 6, 1992,<ref>{{cite news|title=Popular Williams placed in Bucs' Krewe of Honor|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/7633677//|first=Tony|last=Boylan|newspaper=News-Press|page=54|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|date=September 7, 1992|accessdate=November 28, 2016}}{{Open access}}</ref> and owner Hugh Culverhouse on September 5, 1993.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kansas City vs. Tampa Bay: The Game - Headliners|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/7633704//|first=Robin|last=Miller|author-link=Robin Miller (journalist)|newspaper=The Orlando Sentinel|page=15|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|date=September 6, 1993|accessdate=November 28, 2016}}{{Open access}}</ref> No additional members were added before [[Tampa Stadium]] was closed and demolished; when the stadium was demolished in 1998, so was the Krewe.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Tampa Stadium Krewe of Honor'''\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Year\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|No.\n! style=\"width:150px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Name\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n! style=\"width:100px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Tenure\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1991 || 63 || [[Lee Roy Selmon]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1976\u20131984 \n|-\n| \u2014 || [[John McKay (football coach)|John McKay]] || Head Coach || 1976\u20131984\n|-\n| 42 || [[Ricky Bell (running back)|Ricky Bell]] || [[Running Back|RB]] || 1977\u20131981\n|-\n| 1992 || 12 || [[Doug Williams (American football)|Doug Williams]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1978\u20131982\n|-\n| 1993 || \u2014 || [[Hugh Culverhouse]] || Owner || 1976\u20131994\n|}\n\n===Ring of Honor===\nOn November 8, 2009, the team unveiled a new [[Hall of fame|Ring of Honor]] at [[Raymond James Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Edrington|first=Tom|title=Tampa Bay Buccaneers Take Selmon for Their Ring of Honor|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/222658-buccaneers-take-selmon-for-their-ring-of-honor|website=Bleacher Report|date=July 23, 2009|accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n[[File:RaymondJamesStadiumRingofHonor.JPG|thumb|300px|The Ring of Honor at Raymond James Stadium]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ffb\"|Elected to the [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Tampa Bay Buccaneers Ring of Honor'''\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Year\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|No.\n! style=\"width:150px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Name\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Tenure\n|-\n| 2009 || 63 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Lee Roy Selmon]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1976\u20131984 \n|-\n| 2010 || \u2014 || [[John McKay (American football)|John McKay]] || Head Coach || 1976\u20131984\n|-\n| 2011 || 88 || [[Jimmie Giles]] || [[Tight End|TE]] || 1978\u20131986\n|-\n| 2012 || 74 || [[Paul Gruber]] || [[Offensive Tackle|OT]] || 1988\u20131999\n|-\n| 2013 || 99 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Warren Sapp]] || [[Defensive Tackle|DT]] || 1995\u20132003\n|-\n| 2014 || 55 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Derrick Brooks]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1995\u20132008\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2015 || 40 || [[Mike Alstott]] || [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]]  || 1996\u20132007\n|-\n| 12 || [[Doug Williams (American football)|Doug Williams]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1978\u20131982\n|-\n| 2016 || 47 || [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]] || 1993\u20132003\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 2017 || \u2014 || [[Malcolm Glazer]] || Owner || 1995\u20132014\n|-\n| \u2014 || [[Jon Gruden]] || Head Coach || 2002\u20132008\n|-\n| 2018 || \u2014 || style=\"background: